Summary: Timestamps in logs
Class: wish
Difficulty: tricky
Priority: low
Content-type: text/x-html-body

<p>
Timestamps would occasionally be useful in the log files PuTTY
produces.

<p>
Deciding where to put timestamps in SSH packet logs is trivial --
packet starts and Event Log entries.

<p>
Some people want timestamping in raw terminal logs. This is a rather
harder design problem. (See <a href="save-scrollback.html">`save-scrollback'</a>
for a possible solution.)
